page.title: 09WEST END VILLAGE
page.content: West End village hs been described as "a unique backwater of Victorian England".It has a very active Residents' Association which campaigns against the threat to the character of the village from increases in traffic and proposed housing developments.Even the recent transformation of the village pub, the "Prince of Wales",where a "bootleg era" theme has been introduced in the restaurant has generated a great deal of controversy in the community. The largest local concern is Garson Farm which is a nursery-cum-garden centre. The Village Hall is a focal point.The playschool meets there and the pigeon club and the Residents' Association also use it. Housing is expensive for what you get.You have to live there a long time before you become a 'local'.
